{
  "texts": [
    "First in, first out (FIFO) is applied if the bin is full.",
    "To the extent possible, it does, without replacement, sample an equal number of sequences from each bin and otherwise uniformly samples, without replacement, from the bins with elements that have not been sampled until k sequences have been acquired.",
    "Bin current (BC) replay buffer sorts the current batch of sampled sequences into bins with respect to their rewards.",
    "It consists of the following fixed binds with respect to rewards: [0, 0.1], (0.1, 0.2], …, (0.9, 1].",
    "It does, to the extent possible, sample an equal number of sequences from each bin without replacement."
  ]
}